<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>long story • short story</xh5><p> <i>long story—</i>said of a long narrative or account: Miss Sally told us a <u>long story</u> about her friends and about her “comingout party.”</p><p> <div class="note">Note</div> The expression does not correlate in meaning with the phrase <b>tall story</b>—(also: tall tale) a story that is difficult to believe: Their parents yarned over cups of tea, swapped <u>tall stories</u> and books.</p><p> <i>short story—</i>a piece of fiction shorter than a novel: The <u>short story</u> of today is one of two kinds—what is called the Magazine Story; and the newer kind which derives from Chekhov.</p> </entry>
